comments.text:
 @OntarioBirdingOLD  Yep. The scary thing about those bigger cats is they can consider you prey.  Bobcats and Lynne's will generally keep away from you. And usually Mountain lions will shy away from humans but... If you are injured or seem week or turn your back they can and will consider you prey. 

To be totally honest subdivisions are encroaching in thier homes and it is far better to carry a gun in any wilderness setting especially nature trails than ear buds. And never run in any wilderness setting with any larger predators. This includes nature trails in their habitats. On family hikes keep the children between the adults and always carry a big enough gun for what may see you as prey.

But yeah panthers at night? Close to you? Stoke up the fire but never look at it.
